Summary: The course agenda for Real Time Audio-Visual Sensing and Sense Making, taking place January 20-23, 2025, includes a variety of topics and workshops led by instructors Tian Jing and Gary Leung Cheung Chi. The course will cover real time audio-visual sensing systems, video processing and analytics, audio analytics using machine learning, and sense making from multi-modal audio-visual data. The workshops will provide hands-on experience in these areas.

The course agenda for Real Time Audio-Visual Sensing and Sense Making, taught by instructor Gary Leung Cheung Chi, will take place from January 20 to January 23, 2025. The course will include a written assessment test on January 20 at 4:05 PM.
